main event: On 25 June 1960, two pieces of colorless substance, one appearing metallic, fell in Syracuse, New York, after one piece struck the hood of a small automobile.
interesting points: The incident involved two samples forwarded for analysis with no photographs present,The analysis of the materials indicated they were likely glass furnace slag,Analysis from the Wright Air Development Center showed the material contained various elements including calcium and silicon,The incident coincided with the landing of the Sputnik IV carrier vehicle,There were indications that the materials could possibly be foreign space object material.
witness description: No specific witnesses confirmed; reported by civilians.
